Parity_Talk_July-05-2009__FIRE_FOLLOWS_FUN
Hello to all the honest people out there
We're testing our new format for the show. Our strategy is to discuss the more fun topics at the start of the show, and gradually bring in the &quot;Fire and Brimstone&quot; condemnation of humanity later on. This will give the casual listener ample warning about the heavier psychological &quot;Age 25+&quot; preachy and repetitive dialogue that is to come. We have found a better approach and folks who don't like &quot;preaching&quot; can drop away early. This week's show covers various concepts and current events as well as the need for a new &quot;middle class&quot; to emerge in our world. We think we all need to be more balanced people, and avoid the traditions of the master/slave economic feudal system altogether. We need a culture of balance and not one of greed, hedonism, and fun followed by the fire of wickedness and dire consequences. It will take time and effort but we'll end up with a better world.

We comment on the Bahai faith of universal worship, the Venus project.
